field_data.Author: Scott
field_data.Sample Name: Evans1 is el.dep. Ru, Trimi1 is Pt. Nancy are RuO2 sputtered at RT. Jazz2 is 10 nm Ir on Ti
field_data.Removed from vacuum: cycled 18O: Nancy1 and Trimi1 on 19A07, Nancy5, Nancy6, Evans1 on 19A08. Jazz2 sputtered in July

notes: ---- Evans1 01... aborted because I want to wait until the m/z=32 background is down. 02... Clear excess m/z=34 in the start of the CP :D. (link below). But crazy bubble noise right after that. Also, the final ratio looks like 0.5% rather than the natural 0.4%. Similar story for CO2. (second link) 03... Damn, sample showing that same terrible lag on O2 signal again. QMS crashed, new timestamp 21:07:58 ---- Trimi1 04... OCV was +1.15 V vs RHE, consistent with the sample surface being oxidized. Looks like there's a tiny bit of excess O18 right in the beginning! Nothing like the 1 ML of (18)O2 Koper once claims to have seen... Also what is up with these shitty time responses??? 05... Bloody fucking brilliant! For the first time ever, I got the labeled oxygen out on demand! Fuck yes! I switched to CO while holding at ~+1 V vs RHE, i.e., where the oxygen stays in and CO is oxidized. Then I reduced it slowly. when I got to ~0.9 V vs RHE, I got an m/z=46 signal. This is the O18, which had been buried under a layer of O16 during the initial OER, which finally came out. It works! did a CO2 calibration, then a CO strip. CO strip got a bit messed up because accidentally went to OCV just before strip (12000 s). Finally, did an RE_vs_RHE calibration a RE_vs_RHE calibration. RE_vs_RHE=0.719 by CVA but 0.715 by OCV. Biggest discrepency in those two measurements I've seen... I trust the OCV more, as CVA could be affected if there were a little bit of tilt. ---- Nancy1 06... looks fine, a bit bubbly again, but this is a good day, lattice exchange again! Only ran at 60 uA though :(, see below. --- Nancy5 07... shit, I may have jinxed it. No electrolytic contact from WE to CE. Flowed a bit through CE hole. 08... still no. This time, tried sucking and blowing. OCV stable with REisCE, so maybe it'll work. 09... Shit! I was only 60 uA. Also last time, for Nancy1. Trimi1 and Evans1 looks good. This time I changed it right away, so I think Nancy5 can count as if it was done right. Not super pretty, but again, I think you can see a bit of exchange :) --- Nancy6 10... Think I see a tiny bit of exchange, perhaps least so far. --- Jazz2 Okay, now to do a sample that's never seen 18-O, as a control. Searching through the notes here, Jazz2 satisfies that. I don't think it's ever been measured. Today, it will get 5 minutes of OER at 100 uA. Beautiful, no exchange! Something's funky though, it went to 1.7 V vs RHE at first, then down to 1.55 V vs RHE, didn't really stabilize. I would expect Ir to be better. Whatever, doesn't matter. I've proven the m/z=34 excess seen on all the 18-O treated samples today is real exchange. -------------- Links --------------- Evans1 - O2 https://cinfdata.fysik.dtu.dk/sniffer/xyplot.php?type=masstime&xmin=800&xmax=2500&plot_options=checked&matplotlib=checked&title=&xlabel=&left_ylabel=&right_ylabel=&left_ymin=0.4e-12&left_ymax=5.4e-12&right_ymin=-0.5e-10&right_ymax=10e-10&left_plotlist%5B%5D=14433&right_plotlist%5B%5D=14432&chosen_groupC%5B%5D=2019-01-09+18%3A39%3A27 CO2 https://cinfdata.fysik.dtu.dk/sniffer/xyplot.php?type=masstime&xmin=800&xmax=2500&plot_options=checked&matplotlib=checked&title=&xlabel=&left_ylabel=&right_ylabel=&left_ymin=0&left_ymax=0&right_ymin=0&right_ymax=0&left_plotlist%5B%5D=14435&right_plotlist%5B%5D=14436&chosen_group%5B%5D=2019-01-09+18%3A39%3A27 Trimi1 -
